---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title="Cookie Policy - Home Grown Tomatoes"
			description="Cookie Policy for Home Grown Tomatoes."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<main class="legal-page">
			<h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
			<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 23 June 2026</p>

			<p>
				This Cookie Policy explains how Home Grown Tomatoes uses cookies and similar technologies when you visit this website.
			</p>

			<p>
				Home Grown Tomatoes is operated by <strong>RheaNest Media</strong>. In this Cookie Policy, “we”, “us”, and “our” refer to Home Grown Tomatoes and RheaNest Media.
			</p>

			<p>
				Website: <strong>growtomatoesathome.com</strong><br />
				Contact email: <strong>rheanestmedia@gmail.com</strong>
			</p>

			<h2>1. What are cookies?</h2>
			<p>
				Cookies are small text files placed on your computer, phone, tablet, or other device when you visit a website. Cookies can help websites work properly, remember preferences, measure traffic, support affiliate tracking, personalise content, and show or measure advertising.
			</p>

			<p>
				Similar technologies include tracking pixels, tags, scripts, local storage, session storage, web beacons, device identifiers, link decoration, fingerprinting technologies, and other tools that store or access information on your device.
			</p>

			<h2>2. Why we use cookies</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>To make the website work properly.</li>
				<li>To keep the website secure.</li>
				<li>To remember your preferences.</li>
				<li>To remember your cookie consent choices.</li>
				<li>To understand how visitors use the website.</li>
				<li>To improve content, navigation, and user experience.</li>
				<li>To measure which articles, reviews, guides, and product pages are useful.</li>
				<li>To track affiliate link clicks and commissions.</li>
				<li>To deliver, personalise, and measure advertising.</li>
				<li>To measure email marketing and campaign performance.</li>
				<li>To support embedded content, forms, videos, product widgets, and social media features.</li>
				<li>To process purchases, downloads, memberships, or digital product access.</li>
				<li>To prevent spam, abuse, fraud, or security issues.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>3. Types of cookies and technologies we may use</h2>

			<h3>Strictly necessary cookies</h3>
			<p>
				These cookies are required for the website to function, stay secure, remember basic choices, process forms, manage cookie preferences, prevent fraud, or provide services you request.
			</p>

			<h3>Preference cookies</h3>
			<p>
				Preference cookies allow the website to remember choices you make, such as cookie consent settings, display preferences, form preferences, account preferences, or other customisations.
			</p>

			<h3>Analytics cookies</h3>
			<p>
				Analytics cookies help us understand how visitors use the website. They may collect information such as pages visited, time spent on pages, referring websites, country or region, device type, browser type, and interactions with website content.
			</p>

			<p>
				Analytics tools we may use include Google Analytics, Google Search Console, Google Tag Manager, Microsoft Clarity, Bing Webmaster Tools, Plausible, Fathom, Cloudflare Web Analytics, Hotjar, Crazy Egg, Ahrefs Webmaster Tools, Semrush tools, or similar services.
			</p>

			<h3>Affiliate cookies</h3>
			<p>
				Affiliate cookies and tracking links help affiliate partners and affiliate networks identify when a visitor clicks from Home Grown Tomatoes to a third-party website and makes a purchase, signs up, or completes another tracked action.
			</p>

			<p>
				Affiliate cookies may be set by networks or partners such as Amazon Associates, Awin, ShareASale, Impact, CJ Affiliate, Rakuten Advertising, ClickBank, PartnerStack, FlexOffers, Skimlinks, Sovrn Commerce, eBay Partner Network, Etsy affiliate programmes, individual gardening brands, seed suppliers, garden tool retailers, compost suppliers, greenhouse suppliers, grow light suppliers, course providers, software companies, and other affiliate programmes.
			</p>

			<h3>Advertising cookies</h3>
			<p>
				Advertising cookies may be used to show ads, personalise ads, measure ad performance, prevent fraud, limit how often you see an ad, and understand how visitors interact with advertising.
			</p>

			<p>
				Advertising partners may include Google AdSense, Google Ad Manager, Google Ads, Mediavine, Raptive, Ezoic, Monumetric, Media.net, SHE Media, AdThrive, Microsoft Advertising, Meta Ads, Pinterest Ads, TikTok Ads, Taboola, Outbrain, or similar advertising services.
			</p>

			<h3>Social media and embedded content cookies</h3>
			<p>
				If we embed content from third-party platforms, those platforms may set cookies or similar technologies. This may include YouTube, Vimeo, Instagram, Facebook, Pinterest, TikTok, X, Google Maps, Spotify, Apple Podcasts, podcast players, product widgets, adverts, or similar services.
			</p>

			<h3>Email marketing and campaign cookies</h3>
			<p>
				Email marketing tools may use cookies, pixels, or tracking links to measure email opens, clicks, conversions, subscriber preferences, and campaign performance.
			</p>

			<p>
				Email tools may include Mailchimp, Kit, ConvertKit, MailerLite, Brevo, ActiveCampaign, AWeber, GetResponse, Klaviyo, Omnisend, Systeme.io, Beehiiv, Substack, Flodesk, or similar providers.
			</p>

			<h3>Ecommerce and digital product cookies</h3>
			<p>
				If we sell digital products, information products, ebooks, courses, memberships, or downloads, ecommerce and payment platforms may use cookies to process orders, manage checkout, prevent fraud, deliver products, and provide customer support.
			</p>

			<p>
				Ecommerce and payment tools may include Stripe, PayPal, Gumroad, Shopify, WooCommerce, Lemon Squeezy, ThriveCart, SamCart, Payhip, Podia, Teachable, Kajabi, Thinkific, Systeme.io, SendOwl, Easy Digital Downloads, Memberful, Patreon, Buy Me a Coffee, Ko-fi, or similar providers.
			</p>

			<h3>Security and performance cookies</h3>
			<p>
				Security and performance tools may use cookies or similar technologies to protect the website, improve loading speed, detect abuse, prevent spam, and keep the website available.
			</p>

			<p>
				Security and performance providers may include Cloudflare, GitHub, Netlify, Vercel, Google reCAPTCHA, hCaptcha, Akismet, or similar services.
			</p>

			<h2>4. Third-party cookies</h2>
			<p>
				Some cookies may be set by third parties rather than directly by Home Grown Tomatoes. These third parties may collect information about your browsing activity on this website and other websites.
			</p>

			<p>
				Third-party cookies may be used by analytics providers, affiliate networks, advertisers, embedded content providers, social media platforms, email marketing platforms, payment providers, security tools, form providers, ecommerce platforms, and other service providers.
			</p>

			<h2>5. Cookie consent</h2>
			<p>
				Where required by law, we will ask for your consent before placing non-essential cookies on your device. Non-essential cookies may include analytics cookies, advertising cookies, affiliate tracking cookies, social media cookies, and marketing cookies.
			</p>

			<p>
				You should be able to accept or reject non-essential cookies. You should also be able to change your cookie preferences where a cookie consent tool is provided.
			</p>

			<p>
				Strictly necessary cookies may be used without consent because they are needed to provide the website or a service you request.
			</p>

			<h2>6. Managing cookies in your browser</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>You can see what cookies are stored on your device.</li>
				<li>You can delete cookies.</li>
				<li>You can block all cookies.</li>
				<li>You can block third-party cookies.</li>
				<li>You can set preferences for specific websites.</li>
				<li>You can receive a warning before cookies are stored.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				Blocking cookies may affect how this website and other websites work.
			</p>

			<h2>7. Advertising and opt-outs</h2>
			<p>
				If advertising is used on this website, advertising partners may use cookies and similar technologies to show ads and measure results.
			</p>

			<p>
				You may be able to adjust advertising preferences through the relevant advertising provider, your browser, your device settings, our cookie consent tool, or industry opt-out services.
			</p>

			<h2>8. Affiliate tracking and commissions</h2>
			<p>
				When you click an affiliate link, a third party may place a cookie or use a tracking link to record that you came from Home Grown Tomatoes. This allows us to earn a commission if you make a qualifying purchase or complete a qualifying action.
			</p>

			<p>
				Affiliate tracking does not increase the price you pay.
			</p>

			<h2>9. Updates to this Cookie Policy</h2>
			<p>
				We may update this Cookie Policy when we add or remove cookies, analytics tools, affiliate partners, advertising networks, ecommerce tools, email marketing services, or other technologies.
			</p>

			<h2>10. Contact</h2>
			<p>
				For questions about this Cookie Policy, contact:
			</p>

			<p>
				<strong>RheaNest Media</strong><br />
				Website: <strong>growtomatoesathome.com</strong><br />
				Email: <strong>rheanestmedia@gmail.com</strong>
			</p>
		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

